sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious DNS Query for IP Lookup Service APIs
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects DNS queries for IP lookup services such as "api.ipify.org" originating from a non browser process.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Network Connection to IP Lookup Service APIs
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects external IP address lookups by non-browser processes via services such as "api.ipify.org". This could be indicative of potential post compromise internet test activity.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Uncommon Svchost Command Line Parameter
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects instances of svchost.exe running with an unusual or uncommon command line parameter by excluding known legitimate or common patterns.
This could point at a file masquerading as svchost, a process injection, or hollowing of a legitimate svchost instance.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Non Interactive PowerShell Process Spawned
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects non-interactive PowerShell activity by looking at the "powershell" process with a non-user GUI process such as "explorer.exe" as a parent.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Scheduled temp file as task from temp location
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Scheduled temp file as task from temp location

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Schedule Task Creation From Env Variable Or Potentially Suspicious Path Via Schtasks.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects Schtask creations that point to a suspicious folder or an environment variable often used by malware

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Powershell Defender Exclusion
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects requests to exclude files, folders or processes from Antivirus scanning using PowerShell cmdlets

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Scheduled Task Creation via Masqueraded XML File
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of a scheduled task using the "-XML" flag with a file without the '.xml' extension. This behavior could be indicative of potential defense evasion attempt during persistence

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Windows Defender Exclusions Added - PowerShell
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects modifications to the Windows Defender configuration settings using PowerShell to add exclusions

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Non Interactive PowerShell Process Spawned
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects non-interactive PowerShell activity by looking at the "powershell" process with a non-user GUI process such as "explorer.exe" as a parent.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Scheduled Task Creation Via Schtasks.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of scheduled tasks by user accounts via the "schtasks" utility.

signature_matches.name: terminate process
signature_matches.description: host-interaction/process/terminate
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: terminate process
    namespace: host-interaction/process/terminate
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
      - mehunhoff@google.com
      - anushka.virgaonkar@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: span of calls
    mbc:
      - Process::Terminate Process [C0018]
    examples:
      - C91887D861D9BD4A5872249B641BC9F9:0x401A77
      - 9B7CCAA2AE6A5B96E3110EBCBC4311F6:0x10010307
  features:
    - or:
      - api: System.Diagnostics.Process::Kill
      - api: System.Diagnostics.Process::WaitForExit
      - api: System.Diagnostics.Process::WaitForExitAsync
      - api: System.Environment::Exit
      - api: System.Windows.Forms.Application::Exit
      - api: exit
      - api: Exit
      - api: RstrtMgr.RmShutdown
      - and:
        - os: linux
        - api: exit_group
      - and:
        - optional:
          - match: open process
        - or:
          - api: kernel32.TerminateProcess
          - api: ntdll.NtTerminateProcess
          - api: kernel32.ExitProcess
          - api: ZwTerminateProcess
